SPACE EXPLORATION
More than 5000 spacecrafts have been launched into space to gather information since 1957. They include spacecrafts with humans on board, space probes and satellites.
The soviet union(Russia) and the US were originally the main countries exploring space. Many other countries are now involved.
The development of powerful rockets allowed the soviet union to launch the first artificial satellite on October 4,1957. it was called the Sputnik 1 and orbitted around the earth on April 12,1961, the Russian cosmonaut Yurg Gagarin became the first human to circle the earth in space,
The first US satellite ,Explorer 1 went into the orbit on january 31,1958. in 1961, Alan Shepard become the first american to orbit the earth. Landing a man on moon and returning him safely to earth within  a decade was a national goal set by President john F. Kennedy in 1961.
On july 20,1069, astronaut Neil Armstrong stepped omto the moon. Six apollo missions were made to explore the moon between 1969 and 1972. NASA took charge of the US effort during the launch of the first US satellite on January 31,1958.
As time went on, engineers in different fields worked together to develop more sophisticated machinery and equipment to aid in space exploration. some of this machinery include telescopes like the Hubble space Telescope.